<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_æxsærʒæn" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>æxsærʒæn</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>водопад</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>waterfall</q></cit></sense><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>don kæly jæ ræzty ūrs æxsærʒæntæj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>река льется перед ним белыми водопадами</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the river is flowing in front of them like white waterfalls</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>63</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>æxsærʒæny qazt</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>игра водопада</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the waterfall's game</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>49</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>bylæj ajnægmæ — gæpp! aftæ zǧory æxsærʒæn</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>с обрыва на утес — прыг! так бежит водопад</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>jumping from the cliff on the rock, that's how waterfall is running</q></cit><bibl><biblScope>%sЦомак%s 64</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>ūrs fynk kalgæ sæx-sæxgængæ kommæ xawync æxsærʒæntæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>разбрасывая белую пену, с шумом низвергаются в ущелье водопады</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>waterfalls are rushing down with noise and scattering white foam</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Хар._Кадӕг"/><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>don kæly jæ ræzty ūrs æxsærʒæntæj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>река льется перед ним белыми водопадами</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the river is flowing in front of them like white waterfalls</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>63</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>æxsærʒæny qazt</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>игра водопада</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the waterfall's game</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>49</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>bylæj ajnægmæ — gæpp! aftæ zǧory æxsærʒæn</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>с обрыва на утес — прыг! так бежит водопад</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>jumping from the cliff on the rock, that's how waterfall is running</q></cit><bibl><biblScope>%sЦомак%s 64</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>ūrs fynk kalgæ sæx-sæxgængæ kommæ xawync æxsærʒæntæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>разбрасывая белую пену, с шумом низвергаются в ущелье водопады</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>waterfalls are rushing down with noise and scattering white foam</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Хар._Кадӕг"/><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Перебой из *%iæf%i-%isærʒæn%i, как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æxsærfars"/> ‘щека’ из *%iæfsærfars%i. В первой части %iæf%i- из %iāр%i- ‘вода’ с ослаблением гласного в сложении. Во второй части — не сохранившийся самостоятельно глагол *%isærʒ%i- ‘литься’, ‘падать’; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>sarǰ</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>sṛǰ</w><gloss><q>лить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>давать течь</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>harəč-</w><gloss><q>давать падать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>harəz-</w><gloss><q>лить</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="gmh"><lang/><w>selken</w><gloss><q>падать (о жидкости)</q></gloss></mentioned>. Стало быть, %iæxsærʒæn%i из *%iāp-sarjana%i-→*%iāfšārjana%i-. Сохранение %is%i после %ix%i(%if%i) без обычного иранского перебоя → %ih%i говорит о том, что мы имеем дело с очень старым сложным словом; ср. сохранение %is%i в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æfsnajyn"/> рядом с <ref type="xr" target="#entry_najyn"/>. По образованию ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>ābšār</w><gloss><q>водопад</q></gloss></mentioned> из <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>āb</w><gloss><q>вода</q></gloss></mentioned> и <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>šār</w></mentioned> (от <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>šarīdan</w><gloss><q>шумно течь</q></gloss></mentioned>). Перебой %ifš%i → %ixš%i(%ikṣ%i) наблюдается также в сакском, например <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>kṣārma</w></mentioned> из <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>*fšarma</w><gloss><q>стыд</q></gloss></mentioned>, ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7fsarm"/>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It is a version of *%iæf%i-%isærʒæn%i, like <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æxsærfars"/> ‘cheek’ from *%iæfsærfars%i. In the first part there is %iæf%i- from %iāр%i- ‘water’ with the weakening of the vowel in a complex word. In the second part there is the verb*%isærʒ%i- ‘poor’, ‘fall’ which did not remain as a seperate verb; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>sarǰ</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>sṛǰ</w><gloss><q>poor</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>let flow</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>harəč-</w><gloss><q>let fall</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>harəz-</w><gloss><q>poor</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="gmh"><lang/><w>selken</w><gloss><q>fall (of liquid)</q></gloss></mentioned>. Thus, %iæxsærʒæn%i is from *%iāp-sarjana%i- →*%iāfšārjana%i-. The presence of %is%i after %ix%i(%if%i) without a usual Iranian change → %ih%i tells that we are dealing with a very old complex word; cf. the presence of %is%i in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æfsnajyn"/> near <ref type="xr" target="#entry_najyn"/>. By the derivation, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>ābšār</w><gloss><q>waterfall</q></gloss></mentioned> from <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>āb</w><gloss><q>water</q></gloss></mentioned> and <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>šār</w></mentioned> (from <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>šarīdan</w><gloss><q>flow noisily</q></gloss></mentioned>). The change %ifš%i → %ixš%i(%ikṣ%i) is observed also in Khotanese, for example <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>kṣārma</w></mentioned> from <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>*fšarma</w><gloss><q>shame</q></gloss></mentioned>, Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7fsarm"/>.</etym></entry>